        "text": "To explore further? State and Trait curiosity: trait is innate, state can be created by educators...\nIt is said that producing literate and numerate individuals should be the two main focuses of education with curiosity considered an innate trait passed down through our genetic code. It is also said that this inherited trait curiosity varies between individuals; how curious we are at birth and throughout our life. The question of whether one can learn to be more curious is then an interesting, complex idea. Being literate and numerate only seems insufficient in our ever-changing world. Without curiosity, innovation, a core 21st century practice, seems that it might be limited. \n"
